---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import { certifications, education } from '../data/experience';
import { profile } from '../data/profile';
import { absoluteUrl } from '../config/site';

const profilePageJsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'ProfilePage', name: `About ${profile.name}`, url: absoluteUrl('/about/', true),
  mainEntity: { '@type': 'Person', name: profile.name, jobTitle: profile.role, url: absoluteUrl('/', true), sameAs: [profile.github, profile.linkedin], knowsAbout: ['Agentic AI', 'Document intelligence', 'Healthcare interoperability', 'Predictive ML', 'MLOps'] },
};
---
<Layout title="About — Shailesh Dudala" description="The professional origin, engineering principles, and interests behind Shailesh Dudala’s Applied AI work." canonicalPath="/about/" jsonLd={profilePageJsonLd}>
  <section class="about-hero"><div class="shell about-grid"><div><p class="eyebrow">About</p><h1>I learned AI through the discipline of biomedical context.</h1></div><div><p>My early work moved through clinical sensors, genomics, provider data, hospital analytics, and public-health modeling. The lesson was durable: a technically correct result can still fail when its lineage, assumptions, or operating context are invisible.</p><p>That is why I now focus on the layer between model output and accountable action—contracts, evaluation, review, and observability.</p></div></div></section>
  <section class="section origin-story"><div class="shell origin-grid"><div class="origin-line"><span>Biomedical data</span><i></i><span>Healthcare prediction</span><i></i><span>Analytics products</span><i></i><span>Local AI</span><i></i><span>Agentic insurance</span></div><div><p class="eyebrow">The throughline</p><h2>Make uncertainty legible enough for people to act responsibly.</h2><p>Across more than seven years, the models, infrastructure, and products changed. The operating question stayed consistent: what evidence does a person need, what can the system decide, and what should happen when the input does not fit?</p></div></div></section>
  <section class="section paper-section"><div class="shell about-details"><article><span>01</span><h2>What I optimize for</h2><p>Clear failure states, evidence a reviewer can inspect, and outcomes that survive beyond a demonstration.</p></article><article><span>02</span><h2>How I lead</h2><p>I translate ambiguous workflow problems into contracts, evaluation plans, release gates, and shared language across engineering and operations.</p></article><article><span>03</span><h2>What stays private</h2><p>Employer data, production rules, confidential screenshots, credentials, PHI, PII, and proprietary APIs.</p></article></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="shell credentials-grid"><div><p class="eyebrow">Education</p><ul>{education.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}</ul></div><div><p class="eyebrow">Credentials</p><ul>{certifications.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}</ul></div></div></section>
  <section class="section outside-lane"><div class="shell outside-lane"><div><p class="eyebrow">Outside the primary lane</p><h2>Forecasting, quant systems, sports models, and research tooling.</h2></div><p>These interests sharpen how I think about calibration, backtests, uncertainty, and experiment design. They live in the Lab so the primary healthcare and insurance story stays clear.</p><a class="button quiet" href="/lab/">Explore the Lab</a></div></section>
  <section class="section contact-section"><div class="shell contact-layout"><div><p class="eyebrow">Get in touch</p><h2>Have a system where model output needs an accountable path?</h2></div><div class="contact-actions"><a class="button primary" href="/contact/">Start a conversation</a><a href={profile.linkedin}>LinkedIn ↗</a><a href={profile.github}>GitHub ↗</a></div></div></section>
</Layout>
